fix: drop firmware from entry title; map aspect-select to content aspect

Two UX fixes reported from a live install:

1. **Entry title no longer includes firmware version.** Was
   "Lumagen RadiancePro (030225)" — baked in at config-flow time and
   misleading after any OTA update. Now just "Lumagen RadiancePro".
   Firmware lives in `DeviceInfo.sw_version`, which updates live from
   each `!S01` response.

2. **Aspect-ratio selector now shows a best-effort current value.** The
   Lumagen's protocol doesn't expose which aspect *preset* is selected,
   only the detected content aspect. We snap the content_aspect to the
   closest preset label (1.33 -> "4:3", 1.78 -> "16:9", 1.85, 2.35,
   2.40). Will be wrong when the user intentionally picks a mismatched
   preset; a future improvement could track the last selected preset
   separately. Good enough for v0.1.

Updated the happy-path config-flow test to pin the exact title. Added
12 new tests for the aspect mapping covering exact matches, interior
values, clamping, and garbage input.
